sentences: Adolf Scherbaum (23 August 1909 – 2 August 2000) was a trumpet player who specialised in the piccolo trumpet.
Scherbaum was born in the town of Eger, then in Austro-Hungarian Bohemia (now Cheb, Czech Republic).
In 1962/1963, Scherbaum toured in North America, where he performed as a soloist with various orchestras.
He died in 2000 in Sulzbach-Rosenberg, a few days before his 91st birthday.
